{"word":"σκάφος","slug":"σκάφος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>σκάφος1</b></el> <el>(σκά˘φος, ὁ,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:σκάπτω'><el>σκάπτω</el></a>\n<p/><i>a digging, hoeing</i>, <el>σκάφος οἰνέων</el> <i>the time for hoeing</i> vines, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b><p/> <hr/> <el><b>σκάφος2</b></el> <el>(σκά˘φος, ος, εος, τό,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:σκάπτω'><el>σκάπτω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>the hull of a ship</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>alveus</el>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b>:—generally, <i>a ship</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>= <el>σκαφίς</el> II, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}